 the sauce.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_77369\" style=\"width: 1034px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-77369\" data-attachment-id=\"77369\" data-permalink=\"https://dailynexus.com/2017-04-27/cooking-just-like-mama/processed-with-vsco-with-hb2-preset-2/\" data-orig-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/IMG_6417.jpg?fit=2048%2C1570&amp;ssl=1\" data-orig-size=\"2048,1570\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta='{\"aperture\":\"0\",\"credit\":\"\",\"camera\":\"\",\"caption\":\"\",\"created_timestamp\":\"0\",\"copyright\":\"\",\"focal_length\":\"0\",\"iso\":\"0\",\"shutter_speed\":\"0\",\"title\":\"\",\"orientation\":\"0\"}' data-image-title=\"Processed with VSCO with hb2 preset\" data-image-description=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/IMG_6417.jpg?fit=250%2C192&amp;ssl=1\" data-large-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/IMG_6417.jpg?fit=888%2C681&amp;ssl=1\" class=\"size-large wp-image-77369\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/IMG_6417-1024x785.jpg?resize=888%2C681\" alt=\"\" width=\"888\" height=\"681\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/IMG_6417.jpg?resize=1024%2C785&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/IMG_6417.jpg?resize=250%2C192&amp;ssl=1 250w, https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/IMG_6417.jpg?resize=768%2C589&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/IMG_6417.jpg?resize=430%2C330&amp;ssl=1 430w, https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/IMG_6417.jpg?w=2048&amp;ssl=1 2048w, https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/IMG_6417.jpg?w=1776 1776w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 888px) 100vw, 888px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\"><p id=\"caption-attachment-77369\" class=\"wp-caption-text\"><em>Anna Bui / Daily Nexus</em></p></div>\n<p><strong>Ingredients:</strong> Pasta, bacon, egg, cheese, fresh cream, salt, black pepper, garnished with a single egg yolk</p>\n<p><strong>Directions:</strong><br>\nUse the pasta machine.<br>\nBoil the pasta.<br>\nCut the ingredients (the bacon).<br>\nBreak the eggs!<br>\nMix it!: Cheese, fresh cream, and eggs<br>\nStir-fry it (the spaghetti) lightly! (Add the mixture, more salt and black pepper.)</p>\n<p><em>Verdict:</em> Though nothing amazing, the pasta was enjoyable to eat. I must note that the pasta lacked a bit of flavor as I had feared from making the sauce, but the taste of bacon definitely made up for it. I decided to add chicken after making a second plate.</p>\n<p>For my second dish, I originally just wanted to make chicken kabobs. However, after realizing the ingredients were too simple and the flavor of the chicken extremely bland, I found the instructions for making chicken from the chicken and rice recipe to be more promising.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_77368\" style=\"width: 1034px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-77368\" data-attachment-id=\"77368\" data-permalink=\"https://dailynexus.com/2017-04-27/cooking-just-like-mama/processed-with-vsco-with-hb2-preset/\" data-orig-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/IMG_6416.jpg?fit=2048%2C1536&amp;ssl=1\" data-orig-size=\"2048,1536\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta='{\"aperture\":\"0\",\"credit\":\"\",\"camera\":\"\",\"caption\":\"\",\"created_timestamp\":\"0\",\"copyright\":\"\",\"focal_length\":\"0\",\"iso\":\"0\",\"shutter_speed\":\"0\",\"title\":\"\",\"orientation\":\"0\"}' data-image-title=\"Processed with VSCO with hb2 preset\" data-image-description=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/IMG_6416.jpg?fit=250%2C188&amp;ssl=1\" data-large-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/IMG_6416.jpg?fit=888%2C666&amp;ssl=1\" class=\"size-large wp-image-77368\" src=\"https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/IMG_6416-1024x768.jpg?resize=888%2C666\" alt=\"\" width=\"888\" height=\"666\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/IMG_6416.jpg?resize=1024%2C768&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/IMG_6416.jpg?resize=250%2C188&amp;ssl=1 250w, https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/IMG_6416.jpg?resize=768%2C576&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/IMG_6416.jpg?resize=1832%2C1374&amp;ssl=1 1832w, https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/IMG_6416.jpg?resize=1376%2C1032&amp;ssl=1 1376w, https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/IMG_6416.jpg?resize=1044%2C783&amp;ssl=1 1044w, https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/IMG_6416.jpg?resize=632%2C474&amp;ssl=1 632w, https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/IMG_6416.jpg?resize=536%2C402&amp;ssl=1 536w, https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/IMG_6416.jpg?w=2048&amp;ssl=1 2048w, https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/IMG_6416.jpg?w=1776 1776w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 888px) 100vw, 888px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\"><p id=\"caption-attachment-77368\" class=\"wp-caption-text\"><em>Anna Bui / Daily Nexus</em></p></div>\n<p><strong>Ingredients:</strong> chicken, rice, cooking alcohol, cooking sake, broth, sugar, soy sauce</p>\n<p><strong>Directions:</strong><br>\nCut the meat.<br>\nMake stock.<br>\nSauté.<br>\nFry the meat.<br>\nPut on sticks.</p>\n<p><em>Verdict:</em> This dish was pretty difficult to follow, since I made it harder for myself by combining two recipes. However, this one tasted the best, which I believe was due to a really good soy sauce that my family uses.</p>\n<p>For dessert, I chose panna cotta. This was one of my favorite recipes to make in the Cooking Mama game, and I remember wanting to make it in real life.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_77371\" style=\"width: 1034px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-77371\" data-attachment-id=\"77371\" data-permalink=\"https://dailynexus.com/2017-04-27/cooking-just-like-mama/img_d92580143031-1/\" data-orig-file=\"https://i1.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/IMG_D92580143031-1.jpeg?fit=2048%2C1526&amp;ssl=1\" data-orig-size=\"2048,1526\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta='{\"aperture\":\"0\",\"credit\":\"\",\"camera\":\"\",\"caption\":\"\",\"created_timestamp\":\"0\",\"copyright\":\"\",\"focal_length\":\"0\",\"iso\":\"0\",\"shutter_speed\":\"0\",\"title\":\"\",\"orientation\":\"0\"}' data-image-title=\"IMG_D92580143031-1\" data-image-description=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://i1.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/IMG_D92580143031-1.jpeg?fit=250%2C186&amp;ssl=1\" data-large-file=\"https://i1.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/IMG_D92580143031-1.jpeg?fit=888%2C662&amp;ssl=1\" class=\"wp-image-77371 size-large\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/IMG_D92580143031-1-1024x763.jpeg?resize=888%2C662\" alt=\"\" width=\"888\" height=\"662\" srcset=\"https://i1.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/IMG_D92580143031-1.jpeg?resize=1024%2C763&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i1.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/IMG_D92580143031-1.jpeg?resize=250%2C186&amp;ssl=1 250w, https://i1.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/IMG_D92580143031-1.jpeg?resize=768%2C572&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i1.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/IMG_D92580143031-1.jpeg?w=2048&amp;ssl=1 2048w, https://i1.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/IMG_D92580143031-1.jpeg?w=1776 1776w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 888px) 100vw, 888px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\"><p id=\"caption-attachment-77371\" class=\"wp-caption-text\"><em>Anna Bui / Daily Nexus</em></p></div>\n<p><strong>Ingredients:</strong> lemons, strawberries, fresh cream, milk, sugar, vanilla extract, gelatin</p>\n<p><strong>Directions:</strong><br>\nBoil ingredients. (Pour milk then add fresh cream, sugar, vanilla extract and gelatin.)<br>\nPour the liquid then refrigerate.<br>\nSlice (the strawberries).<br>\nSqueeze the lemon.<br>\nUse the mixer (blend the lemon juice and strawberries).<br>\nPut the filling into dish.</p>\n<p><em>Verdict:</em> I looked at the final product and honestly didn’t even want to give it a taste test. The entire process was so improvised because I had no idea what quantities to add into the mixture. I took a small bite, and, well, it’s edible. I didn’t take another bite.<br>\nAs I was cleaning up, my sister started eating it, claiming that it was actually really good, so it’s important to recognize that taste is relative when it comes to “reviewing” food.</p>\n<p>Though I ended up with very mixed results, this actually was a very fun experience, as I had no idea what to expect from each dish. With instructions so broad, each attempt will be unique and the results will not always be the same. Thus, I suggest giving this Cooking Mama taste test a chance; you’ll definitely be in for a surprise. Though I must conclude one thing from this: I do not cook better than Mama.</p><div class=\"h5ab-print-button-container\"><div class=\"h5ab-print-button h5ab-print-button-left\" style=\"cursor: pointer; color: #555\"><i class=\"fa fa-print fa-lg\"></i>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span>Print</span></div></div>\n<div class=\"sharedaddy sd-sharing-enabled\"><div class=\"robots-nocontent sd-block sd-social sd-social-icon sd-sharing\"><h3 class=\"sd-title\">Share this:</h3><div class=\"sd-content\"><ul><li class=\"share-facebook\"><a rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\" data-shared=\"sharing-facebook-77367\" class=\"share-facebook sd-button share-icon no-text\" href=\"https://dailynexus.com/2017-04-27/cooking-just-like-mama/?share=facebook\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Click to share on Facebook\"><span></span><span class=\"sharing-screen-r